    "description": "Harima Chemicals Group, Inc. primarily manufactures and sells various chemicals in Japan, China, rest of Asia, South and North America, Europe, and internationally. The company operates through Resins and Chemicals, Paper Chemicals, Electronics Materials segments. The Resins and Chemicals products segment offers resins for paints, resins for printing inks, emulsifiers for synthetic rubber, resins for adhesives, and tall oil products. The Paper Chemicals segment provides paper strength agents, sizing agents, coating agents, and barrier coating agents. The Electronics Materials segment offers soldering materials, brazing materials for heat exchangers, and functional resins for semiconductors. It also manufactures and sells industrial detergents, etc.; and provides real estate management services. The company was formerly known as Harima Chemicals, Inc. and changed its name to Harima Chemicals Group, Inc. in October 2012. The company was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
